/\*\*  
 \* Create a price in Stripe for the AI Faceless Video product.  
 \* @param {number} amount \- The price amount in cents.  
 \* @param {string} currency \- The currency of the price (e.g., 'usd').  
 \* @returns {Promise\<string\>} \- The ID of the created price.  
 \*/  
const createStripePrice \= async (amount, currency) \=\> {  
  try {  
    const product \= await stripe.products.create({  
        name: 'AI faceless Video',  
      });  
    const price \= await stripe.prices.create({  
      unit\_amount: amount,  
      currency: currency,  
      product: product.id,  
    });  
    return price.id;  
  } catch (error) {  
    console.error('Error creating Stripe price:', error.message);  
    throw new Error('Failed to create Stripe price');  
  }  
};

module.exports \= { createStripePrice };

/\*\*  
 \* Controller to handle payment-related operations.  
 \*/  
class PaymentController {  
  /\*\*  
   \* Create a new price using Stripe.  
   \* @param {object} req \- The request object.  
   \* @param {object} res \- The response object.  
   \*/  
  async createPrice(req, res) {  
    try {  
      const { amount, currency } \= req.body;

      if (\!amount || \!currency) {  
        return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Amount and currency are required' });  
      }

      const priceId \= await createStripePrice(amount, currency);  
      res.status(201).json({ priceId });  
    } catch (error) {  
      console.error('Error creating price:', error.message);  
      res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to create price' });  
    }  
  }  
}

module.exports \= new PaymentController();

**\# ClipFlowAI \- AI Faceless Video Creation Tool**

**\#\# Project Description**

ClipFlowAI is a tool designed to automate the creation of engaging, faceless videos suitable for platforms like TikTok, Instagram Reels, and YouTube Shorts. Users provide a text prompt, and the system generates a video with voiceover, captions, and background visuals. The tool leverages AI and automation to streamline video creation, making it accessible even without video editing skills.

**\#\# Key Features**

\*   **\*\*AI-Powered Video Generation:\*\*** Creates videos from text prompts.  
\*   **\*\*Voiceover Generation:\*\*** Converts text to speech for voiceovers.  
\*   **\*\*Caption Generation:\*\*** Automatically generates video captions.  
\*   **\*\*Multi-Platform Publishing:\*\*** Supports publishing to TikTok, Instagram, and YouTube.  
\* **\*\*Payment\*\***: It is possible to pay to create a video.  
\*   **\*\*Analytics Dashboard:\*\*** Provides insights into video performance.  
\*   **\*\*User Authentication:\*\*** Secure user accounts with signup and login.

 \* Create a new video  
 \* @param {object} videoData \- Video data

export const createVideo \= async (videoData) \=\> {  
  const { platforms, ...videoDetails } \= videoData;  
  const script \= videoData.script || '';  
  const music \= videoData.music || '';  
  const voiceProfile \= videoData.voiceProfile || '';  
  const subtitles \= videoData.subtitles || '';  
  const scheduled\_at \= videoData.scheduled\_at || null; // Add this line

  // Insert video record  
  const { data: video, error: videoError } \= await supabase  
    .from(VIDEOS\_TABLE)  
    .insert(\[  
      {  
        ...videoDetails,  
        created\_at: new Date().toISOString(),  
        status: 'pending',  
        script,  
        music,  
        voice\_profile: voiceProfile,  
        subtitles,  
        scheduled\_at // Add this line  
      }  
    \])  
    .select()  
    .single();

  if (videoError) {  
    throw videoError;  
  }

  // If platforms are specified, insert platform records  
  if (platforms && platforms.length \> 0) {  
    const platformRecords \= platforms.map(platform \=\> ({  
      video\_id: video.id,  
      name: platform,  
      status: 'pending'  
    }));

    const { error: platformError } \= await supabase  
      .from(PLATFORMS\_TABLE)  
      .insert(platformRecords);

    if (platformError) {  
      throw platformError;  
    }  
  }

  // Return the created video with platforms  
  return getVideoById(video.id);  
};
